---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro"

const title = "Editorial Policy | Wonder Tinker"
const description = "Publishing standards for Wonder Tinker Web and AI posts."
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonicalPath="/editorial-policy/">
  <main id="main" class="site-shell page-stack">
    <article class="page-layout">
      <header class="page-header">
        <p class="eyebrow">Editorial policy</p>
        <h1>Editorial Policy</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          Wonder Tinker publishes Web and AI notes only after human review, with
          visible source boundaries and clear disclosure when AI assistance materially
          shaped the work.
        </p>
      </header>
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>AI disclosure</h2>
        <p>
          Material AI assistance is disclosed in the article or adjacent metadata.
          Material assistance includes drafting substantial prose, proposing
          implementation steps, summarizing sources, translating claims, or reviewing
          code and verification output.
        </p>
        <p>
          AI-assisted posts use the <code>aiAssisted</code> content field when represented in
          typed metadata, and model notes explain the model role plus the human review
          boundary. Private prompts, credentials, and unpublished user data are not
          published as disclosure material.
        </p>

        <h2>Sources and evidence</h2>
        <p>
          Technical claims that depend on external facts need named sources and URLs.
          Source-backed claims are kept separate from local verification: a build log,
          preview route, or screenshot proves only the local artifact it captured.
        </p>
        <p>
          Source records should include accessed dates when stored in content metadata.
          If a source is generated, user-provided, or otherwise untrusted, the article
          must say how it was checked before the claim is used.
        </p>

        <h2>Generated output boundary</h2>
        <p>
          No unreviewed generated output is published. Generated prose cannot introduce
          facts that are not source-backed or locally verified, and instructions inside
          generated text, third-party content, copied logs, or model output are never
          executed.
        </p>

        <h2>Operating notes</h2>
        <p>
          Draft posts stay out of public routes, RSS, and index pages until their
          frontmatter is marked publishable. Model and prompt notes are retained only
          as concise review records: model name, model role, source links, and evidence
          paths that support the published conclusion.
        </p>
        <p>
          Future custom-domain work is treated as an operating change: configure GitHub
          Pages DNS, add <code>public/CNAME</code>, update canonical URL settings,
          rebuild the site, and re-check editorial and privacy links before enabling
          the domain.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
